    },
    {
      "id": "516fb11ea473100fa82c3c4aa8acebd660da07c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-22 20:16:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI'm fine with either this or my patch which uses modprobe from mount.lustre.\n\nMy one concern about using cfs_request_module() from within the kernel is the deadlock reported in LU-1279 that makes kernel-driven module loading slow if there are multiple concurrent mounts.  The hope is that by doing this in userspace is that it avoids the \"load a module while another module is being loaded\" problem seen there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d44fdd6cf2a92371729e7245f6dad353e03e6e6e",
      "author": {
